---
By: Papa Ramdas
Locus:
  Page: 368
  Verse: 2
Tags:
  - Power
---
We try to acquire so many things of the world, but find no peace in them.
When your mind is flitting from object to object. ...it lives in a state of
restlessness which is itself misery. After possession of an object, comes
care and anxieties; after a loss, grief and pain.
